{{Infobox protected area | name = Claytor Lake State Park | iucn_category = III | photo = ClaytorLakeStatePark.png | photo_caption = Photo of sunrise at Claytor Lake State Park, Virginia, USA | location = [[Pulaski County, Virginia]], [[United States|USA]] | nearest_city = | map = Virginia#USA | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Claytor Lake State Park in [[Virginia]] | map_width = | coordinates = {{coords|37|3|32|N|80|37|42|W|display=inline, title}} | area_acre = 472 | established = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Virginia Department of Conservation and Recreation]] }}
'''Claytor Lake State Park''' is a {{convert|472|acre|adj=on}} [[state park]] in [[Pulaski County, Virginia]]. The park is located on [[Claytor Lake]], a {{convert|4500|acre|km2|adj=on}}, {{convert|21|mi|km|adj=mid|-long}} reservoir on the [[New River (Kanawha River)|New River]] formed by [[Claytor Dam]], which is used to generate [[hydroelectric]] power by the [[Appalachian Power|Appalachian Power Company]]. The reservoir is named for [[W. Graham Claytor]] (1886–1971) of nearby [[Roanoke, Virginia|Roanoke]], a former vice president of Appalachian Power who supervised construction of the dam and creation of the lake.
Claytor Lake State Park has hiking trails, a freshwater swimming beach, boating and fishing opportunities, a full-service marina, visitor center, concession, lakeside cabins, camping with full hookups, interpretive programs and six rental shelters accommodating large groups.
The [[Haven B. Howe House]] is used as a Nature Exhibit Center that focuses on the lake’s wildlife habitat.<ref name=VAnom>{{cite web|url=http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/Counties/Pulaski/077-0047_Haven_B_Howe_House_Nomination_2005_final.pdf|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: Haven B. Howe House|author=Marc C. Wagner and Jean O. McRae |date= April 2005|publisher=Virginia Department of Historic Resources}}</ref> It was added to the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2008.<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref>
