[[File:Hepburn Wind Farm 2011.jpg|thumb|[[Turbine]]s at the [[Hepburn Wind Project]]]] [[File:Westmill Solar Cooperative 1.jpg|thumbnail|right|Visitors at a [[Westmill Solar Co-operative]] open day at Westmill Solar Park]]
This is a '''list of energy cooperatives'''. A [[cooperative]] is an autonomous association of persons who [[voluntary association|voluntarily]] cooperate for their mutual social, economic, and cultural benefit.<ref name="ica-principles">[http://www.ica.coop/coop/principles.html Statement on the Cooperative Identity.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120204081503/http://www.ica.coop/coop/principles.html |date=2012-02-04 }} ''[[International Cooperative Alliance]].''</ref> Cooperatives include non-profit community organizations and businesses that are owned and managed by the people who use its services (a [[consumer cooperative]]) or by the people who work there (a [[worker cooperative]]) or by the people who live there (a [[housing cooperative]]), hybrids such as worker cooperatives that are also consumer cooperatives or [[credit union]]s, multi-stakeholder cooperatives such as those that bring together civil society and local actors to deliver community needs, and second and third tier cooperatives whose members are other cooperatives.
A 2009 study found that 23% of the newly founded cooperatives in Germany were in the energy sector. These cooperatives primarily operate wind farms, bioenergy and photovoltaic farms with local and regional scope.<ref>{{cite book|title=Climate Change Governance|date=2013|publisher=Springer|location=Berlin|isbn=978-3-642-29831-8|page=110|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gQnNpayz04cC&lpg=PA110&dq=%22energy%20cooperatives%22&pg=PA110#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>
==Energy cooperatives== * * [[Baywind Energy Co-operative]] * [[Brighton Energy Co-operative]] * [[Community wind energy]] – projects are locally owned by farmers, investors, businesses, schools, utilities, or other public or private entities who utilize wind energy to support and reduce energy costs to the local community * [[Enercoop]] * [[Energy4All]] * [[Ecopower (cooperative)|Ecopower]] * [[Fox Islands Electric Cooperative]] * [[Hepburn Wind Project]] * [[National Wind]] * [[Native Wind]] * [[Som Energia]] * [[Vineyard Power Co-operative]] * [[Westmill Solar Co-operative]] * [[Westmill Wind Farm Co-operative]] * [[WindShare]] ; Switzerland * [[Elektra Birseck Münchenstein]] ; Germany In 2014 Germany had close to 1000<ref>[[:de:Bürgerenergiegenossenschaft]]</ref>{{Better source|reason=per WP:CIRCULAR|date=February 2017}} energy cooperatives, among them: *Bürger Energie Region Regensburg eG (BERR)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.berregensburg.de|title=Start|website=www.berregensburg.de}}</ref> *Bürgerwerke eG<ref>{{cite web|url=https://buergerwerke.de|title=Bürgerwerke - 100 % Ökostrom – Von Bürgern für Bürger -|website=buergerwerke.de}}</ref> *BürgerEnergie Buxtehude eG<ref>buergerenergie-buxtehude.de</ref> *BürgerEnergieAltmark eG<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buerger-energie-altmark.de/|title=BürgerEnergieAltmark eG, Altmark|website=www.buerger-energie-altmark.de}}</ref> *EnergieWende Erlangen und Erlangen-Höchstadt E- WERG eG<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ewerg.de/|title=EWERG eG - Bürgergenossenschaft EnergieWende Erlangen und Erlangen-Höchstadt eG|website=www.ewerg.de}}</ref> *Elektrizitätswerke Schönau<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ews-schoenau.de/|title=atomstromlos. klimafreundlich. bürgereigen. - EWS Schönau|website=EWS Schönau}}</ref> *[[Greenpeace Energy]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.greenpeace-energy.de/|title=Privatkunden|publisher=}}</ref> *HEG Heidelberger Energiegenossenschaft eG<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heidelberger-energiegenossenschaft.de/|title=Home - HEG Heidelberger Energiegenossenschaft eG|first=Super|last=User|website=www.heidelberger-energiegenossenschaft.de}}</ref> *Neue Energien West- NEW eG<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neue-energien-west.de/|title=NEW – Neue Energien West eG - NEW - Neue Energien West eG, Bürger Energiegenossenschaft West eG im Landkreis Neustadt a. d. Waldnaab und der Stadt Weiden i. d. Oberpfalz|website=www.neue-energien-west.de}}</ref> *Raiffeisen Bürger–Energiegenossenschaft Bliesgau eG<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beg-bliesgau.de/|title=BuergerEnergieGenossenschaft Bliesgau - Startseite|first=Super|last=User|website=www.beg-bliesgau.de}}</ref> *Regionalstrom Franken eG<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regionalstrom-franken.de/|title=Regionalstrom Franken|website=Regionalstrom Franken eG}}</ref> *Ur- Strom BürgerEnergieGenossenschaft Mainz eG<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.urstrom.com/|title=Urstrom eG Bürgerenergiegenossenschaft|website=www.urstrom.com}}</ref> *Windfang eG Frauenenergiegemeinschaft<ref>{{cite web|url=http://s477174211.website-start.de|title=Windfang eG - Frauen im Aufwind - Home|website=s477174211.website-start.de}}</ref>
